Case Study: The Group Chat Leak

-Scenario: A student vents aggressively about a professor in a "private" class WhatsApp group after receiving a poor grade.
-The Problem: A peer screenshots the messages and forwards them to the department head.
-Consequence: The student faces disciplinary action for harassment and violating the school’s code of conduct.

What to Do Differently

-The 24-Hour Rule: Wait a full day before sending any digital message while angry.
-Assume Zero Privacy: Treat every "private" text as if it will eventually be seen by your dean or boss.
-Use Formal Channels: Address grading frustrations via a polite, scheduled office hour visit or a professional email.
-Vent Offline: If you must complain, do it in person to a trusted friend—never leave a digital paper trail.
